  , issueCommentBody =
      "Today on the same cluster, I removed our original (smaller) server so that the cluster now consists of 5 nodes with equivalent hardware. I then re-configured the cluster to have 5 shards, with 5 replicas. Initially, everything worked perfectly and 4 of the 5 shards successfully rebalanced. Then, with 4 replicas of shard 3 green, and the fifth one backfilling, the shard changed which server it listed as its \"primary replica,\" went into \"outdated reads\" mode, and set the other replicas to \"backfilling\":\r\n\r\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/690517/13545593/fc45a70c-e245-11e5-890a-87f0bb33c326.png)\r\n\r\nThen, as soon as 4 of the 5 replicas had caught up, it switched its \"primary replica\" again, putting the table back in \"outdated reads\" mode:\r\n\r\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/690517/13545597/27f98eb8-e246-11e5-9f0a-a1fec1e5dbb1.png)\r\n\r\nRight now I'm waiting for this new strategy to finish balancing, but I'm not too optimistic about about it being able to finish."
